marked: This cluster located in the caudal part of the intraparietal sulcus and corresponded to the most caudomedial part of the angular gyrus

The number of subjects who showed significant activation in the respective area were as follows; superior parietal lobule: 18 (bilateral), intraparietal sulcus: 18 (bilateral: 16, right: 2), dorsal premotor area: 18 (bilateral: 16, left: 2), pre-SMA: 7 (midline: 6, left: 1), ventral prefrontal cortex: 16 (bilateral: 8, left: 5, right: 3), precentral gyrus: 6 (left), cerebellum: 13 (bilateral: 9, right: 4).
